{% extends "docs/_layout.twig" %}
{% block doc_content %}
    <h1>Security</h1>
    <p>
        Rhapsody is built with security in mind and includes several features to protect your application from common vulnerabilities.
    </p>

    <h2>CSRF Protection</h2>
    <p>
        Cross-Site Request Forgery (CSRF) attacks trick users into performing unwanted actions. Rhapsody makes protection easy.
    </p>
    <p>
        The <code>VerifyCsrfTokenMiddleware</code> runs globally on every request. It automatically validates CSRF tokens for all <code>POST</code> requests (and other “unsafe” methods like <code>PUT</code>, <code>PATCH</code>, <code>DELETE</code>). If the token is missing or invalid, the request is aborted with a <strong>419 Page Expired</strong> error.
    </p>

    <h3>Adding the CSRF Token to Forms</h3>
    <p>
        Include the <code>csrf_field()</code> Twig function inside every form that submits with <code>method="POST"</code> (or uses a spoofed method). This generates a hidden input containing the user’s unique token.
    </p>
    <pre><code class="language-twig">&lt;form action="/profile/update" method="POST"&gt;
    {{ csrf_field() }}
    &lt;!-- other fields --&gt;
    &lt;button type="submit"&gt;Update Profile&lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/form&gt;</code></pre>

    <h3>CSRF for JSON APIs</h3>
    <p>
        For JSON requests, include the token in the request body under the key <code>_token</code>. The middleware intelligently looks for the token in both <code>$_POST</code> and the parsed JSON payload.
    </p>
    <pre><code class="language-json">{
    "_token": "generated_token_here",
    "name": "John Doe"
}</code></pre>

    <h3>CSRF Global Middleware</h3>
    <p>
        The <code>VerifyCsrfTokenMiddleware</code> is included in the <code>global</code> array in <code>config/middleware.php</code>. It runs automatically on every matched request. You can add your own global middleware there as well.
    </p>

    <h3>Excluding URIs from CSRF Verification</h3>
    <p>
        You can exclude certain URIs (e.g., webhooks) by editing the <code>$except</code> array in <code>app/Middleware/VerifyCsrfTokenMiddleware.php</code>. Wildcards (<code>*</code>) are supported.
    </p>

    <h2>Password Hashing</h2>
    <p>
        The framework uses PHP's native <code>password_hash()</code> and <code>password_verify()</code> for all user authentication. Passwords are never stored in plain text and are protected with a modern, secure hashing algorithm. See <code>app/Models/User.php</code> and <code>app/Controllers/AuthController.php</code> for implementation details.
    </p>
{% endblock %}